how can i stop being so impatient ive recently come of my pill after being on it for years and we're trying for a baby i ovulate next friday and its driving me crazy im so frustrated that i have to wait so long and also ive got it in my head that i'll fall pregnant at a drop of a hat and i know that wont happen but part of me believes that all my friends fell pregnant so quickly that it'll happen to me how can i stop thinking about baby making and relax over it all im ging crazy thanks in advance lol if your like me then you'll never relax i also been on the pill for years and come off of it months ago and all my family have all had kids and it's taking me ages first i was excited because at last i thought ' i'm going to have a baby' and then after waiting month after month i got disappointed now i've learnt to stay positive i've learnt that you'll go through ups and downs with it but you need to keep your head up when or if that happens you never know you maybe one of the lucky ones and may conceive straight away anyway good to you Fertility awareness Knots Landing Oral contraceptive Birth control Alanis Morissette Shaggy dog story Humphrey Bogart Pregnancy Baby Blues Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Eddie Guerrero Sharon Tate Menstrual cycle Social rule Charmed Neighbours EastEnders Jon Secada Abortion debate AFI 100 Years series Futurama (TV series - season 2) Sleeping Murder 2000 Australian Grand Prix Kodocha Days of our Lives Charles Ives Development of Darwin's theory Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 My Family (television) R.E.M. (band) Friends Dog training The Inside John Sheridan (Babylon 5) Kill Bill 1957 World Series Jean Grey Max Martin Four square Dancing at Lughnasa Saved by the Bell Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Who Shot Mr. Burns? Caffeine Cleveland Browns Sonic the Hedgehog Aerial (dance move) Emergency contraception Everwood Alois Hitler Breastfeeding Cliff Richard Beavis and Butt-head Lisa the Vegetarian Phoebe Halliwell Norway 